'''愛'''（'''''Love'''''）是美國藝術家[[羅伯特·印第安納|羅伯特·印第安納]]製作的一個流行藝術標誌。該標誌使用Didone字體寫出英文「LOVE」，其中「O」 呈傾斜，和「V」連成一線。最初的這一設計使用紅色字母和綠色及藍色背景。這一設計最初被用作[[現代藝術博物館|現代藝術博物館]]在1965年的聖誕賀卡。該設計很快就開始流行，並登上美國郵票<ref>(1) {{cite web|url=https://stamps.org/userfiles/file/albums/Love.pdf|title=Love|year=2011|pages=1–13|publisher=[[American_Philatelic_Society|American Philatelic Society]]|accessdate=2018-01-07|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160803182329/http://stamps.org/userfiles/file/albums/Love.pdf|archivedate=2016-08-03}}<br>(2) {{cite journal|url=http://www.uspostalbulletins.com/PDF/Vol93_Issue20904_19721221.pdf|title=8-Cent Special Stamp for Someone Special|work=Postal Bulletin|date=1972-12-21|number=20904|page=3|publisher=[[United_States_Postal_Service|United States Postal Service]]|location=Washington, D.C.|accessdate=2018-05-12|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180513011555/http://www.uspostalbulletins.com/PDF/Vol93_Issue20904_19721221.pdf|archivedate=2018-05-13}}<br>(3) {{cite web|title=Love (1973)|work=Art of the Stamp|publisher=[[Smithsonian_Institution|Smithsonian]] [[National_Postal_Museum|National Postal Museum]]|url=http://www.postalmuseum.si.edu/artofthestamp/SubPage%20table%20images/artwork/love/1973%20Love/love1973.htm|accessdate=2018-01-18|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180107022641/https://postalmuseum.si.edu/artofthestamp/subpage%20table%20images/artwork/love/1973%20Love/love1973.htm|archivedate=2018-01-07}}<br>(4) {{cite web|last=Piazza|first=Daniel|date=2008-08-15|url=https://arago.si.edu/category_2034469.html|title=Love Issue|work=Arago: People, Postage & The Post ([[Philately|Philately]])|location=Washington, D.C.|publisher=[[Smithsonian_Institution|Smithsonian]] [[National_Postal_Museum|National Postal Museum]]|accessdate=2018-05-12|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203082032/http://arago.si.edu/category_2034469.html|archivedate=2016-02-03}}<br>(5) {{cite web|first=Michael|last=Baadke|url=https://www.linns.com/insights/stamp-collecting-basics/1998/november/special-stamps-to-convey-special-messages-.html|title=Special stamps to convey special messages|date=1998-11-30|work=Linn's Stamp News|publisher=Amos Media Company|accessdate=2018-05-13|quote=The first U.S. Love stamp was an 8¢ issue (Scott 1475) that resembled many commemorative stamps from 1973: it was multicolor and about twice the size of the 8¢ Dwight D. Eisenhower definitive stamp (Scott 1394) issued a couple of years before. .... The Postal Service printed 320 million of those Love stamps, about twice the normal print run for a commemorative stamp in those days. .... A publication of the USPS Stamps Division described the issue as "A Special Stamp for Someone Special."|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118132420/https://www.linns.com/insights/stamp-collecting-basics/1998/november/special-stamps-to-convey-special-messages-.html|archivedate=2018-01-18}}<br>(6) {{cite web|url=http://swapmeetdave.com/Stamps/FDC/1973/1475cc.jpg|title=1973 "Love" stamp first day of issue cover|format=photograph|date=1973-01-26|work=FDCs of Commemorative Stamps ~ 1973|publisher=SwapMeetDave|accessdate=2018-05-13|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180513152636/http://swapmeetdave.com/Stamps/FDC/1973/1475cc.jpg|archivedate=2018-05-13}}</ref>。1970年，[[印第安納波利斯藝術博物館|印第安納波利斯藝術博物館]]展示了第一個該造型的雕塑<ref name="Love IMA">[http://www.imamuseum.org/collections/artwork/love-indiana-robert "Love" (sculpture)] {{Wayback|url=http://www.imamuseum.org/collections/artwork/love-indiana-robert |date=20141221124019 }}, Explore Art: IMA Collections. Retrieved 5 March 2013.</ref>。現在世界各地均有同樣外觀的雕塑。
